Sure! The new issue is requesting the creation of a C# .Net Azure Function Project that will use the SteamKit package to connect to Steam, login, start Dota2, and create a Dota2 custom lobby. 

To address this issue, you can follow these steps:
1. Create a new C# .Net Azure Function Project.
2. Install the SteamKit package in the project.
3. Write the code to connect to Steam, login, start Dota2, and create a Dota2 custom lobby.
4. Test the code to ensure it is working as expected.
5. Commit the code to the cautious-doodle repository.
6. Close the issue once the code has been committed.

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.
